### Elf Traits
***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Dexterity score increases by 2.

***Age.*** Can live up to 3000 years

***Alignment.***

***Creature Type.*** You are Humanoid.

***Size.*** You are Medium.

***Speed.***

#### High Elf
***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Intelligence score increases by 1.

#### Night Elf
***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Wisdom score increases by 1.

***Darkvision.***

***Fleet of Foot.*** Your base walking speed increases to 35 feet.

***Shadowmeld.*** You gain advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks when in dim light or darkness.

***Mask of the Wild.*** You can attempt to hide even when you are only lightly obscured by foliage, heavy rain, falling snow, mist, and other natural phenomena.

***Nature Resistance.*** Less prone to snags due to thorns, sharp rocks, cold, etc. due to wearing little clothing.

\pagebreak

## Forsaken
Ichor of undeath

***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Charisma score increases by 2 and your Constitution score increases by 1.

***Age.*** Forsaken are preserved in whatever state they were raised and thus do not age. However, decay and rot can cause their body to degrade if they do not perform upkeep, and the chill of undeath can affect the mind's sanity, leading to similar issues as a mortal's advancing age.

***Alignment.*** Forsaken typically lack the empathy required to be good and thus tend towards evil or at best neutrality.

***Creature Type.*** You are Undead. This causes a number of game effects to affect you differently, as seen in the Undead Players sidebar.

***Size.*** You are Medium.

***Speed.*** Your base walking speed is 30 feet.

***Undead Fortitude.*** When you are reduced to 0 hit points but not killed outright, you can drop to 1 hit point instead, unless the damage is radiant. You can't use this feature again until you finish a long rest.

***Undead Nature.*** As an undead, you have the following properties:
- You are immune to poison damage, disease, and the poisoned condition.
- You don't need to eat, drink, or breathe, though you can choose to do so.
- You do not need to sleep, and magic can't put you to sleep. Instead, you fill your short and long rests with light activity to gain their benefits.
- You cannot benefit from certain spells, such as *cure wounds*, and you are immune to other spells such as *crown of madness* or *dominate person* as they specifically target humanoids. See the **Spells By Affected Creature Type** sidebar in Chapter ?: Spells.

Painful Light. Incapacited by radiant damage and healing magic.


False Appearance. You may, as an action, collapse your form into a pile of bones. While you remain motionless, you are indistinguishable from a normal pile of bones. In this state, you are prone and your speed is 0.



However certain spells have no effect on you, namely healing spells like cure wounds or healing word, as well as other spells that specify that they have no effect on Constructs or Undead.


Carrion Eater. You gain nutrition from corpses, ignoring any detriment. You may consume dead or rotting bodies and flesh to fulfill your food requirement, and you are immune to any diseases or effects that would render you poisoned when you do so.


Undead Fortitude. If damage reduces you to 0 hit points, you must make a Constitution saving throw with a DC of 5 + half the damage taken, unless the damage is radiant or from a critical hit. On a success, you drop to 1 hit point instead. You regain usage of this feat after a short rest.

SUBTYPES: Fresh Raise (Appear almost normal), Decaying (Normal), Mummified, Skeletal (False Appearance as a skeleton, disadv on Str)

> ##### Undead Players


Cannibalism. Using 1 minute, you can cannibalize the corpse of a humanoid that has been dead for less than 1 hour. When done, you regain a number of hit point sequal to your level + your Constitution modifier. Once you use this trait, you can't use it again until you finish a short rest.

Shadow Resistance. You have resistance to necrotic damage.

Undead. You have two creature types: humanoid and undead. You can be affected by a game effect if it works on either of your creature types. In addition, you gain the following benefits:

Will of the Forsaken. You have advantage on saving throws against being charmed or frightened as well as effects that turn undead. Additionally, magic can't put you to sleep.

