## Tauren
https://www.dandwiki.com/wiki/Tauren_(5e_Race)
### Tauren
***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Strength score increases by 2, and your Wisdom increases by 1.

***Age.***

***Alignment.***

***Creature Type.*** You are Humanoid.

***Size.*** Your size is Large. 

***Speed.*** Your base walking speed is 35 feet.

***Low-Light Vision.*** 

***Horns.*** Your horns are natural melee weapons, which you can use to make unarmed strikes. If you hit with them, you deal piercing damage equal to 1d8 + your Strength modifier, instead of the bludgeoning damage normal for an unarmed strike.

***Bull in a China Shop.*** Adv on Str, Disadv on Dex checks (Three fingered hands: two fingers, one thumb)

***Goring Rush.*** Immediately after you use the Dash action on your turn and move at least 20 feet, you can make one melee attack with your horns as a bonus action.

***Hammering Horns.*** Immediately after you hit a creature with a melee attack as part of the Attack action on your turn, you can use a bonus action to attempt to shove that target with your horns. The target must be no more than one size larger than you and within 5 feet of you. Unless it succeeds on a Strength saving throw against a DC equal to 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Strength modifier, you push it up to 10 feet away from you.

***Plainsrunning.*** Your base movement speed is doubled when considering distance traveled overland.

***Tauren Endurance.*** Your hit point maximum increases by 1, and it increases by 1 every time you gain a level.

***Languages.*** Taur-ahe, Common

